{"timestamp": "2025-12-02 20:18:42.393144", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission successful.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"web_server_0\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"link_bandwidth_throttling\"]\n\nRecommended next steps (optional):\n- On web_server_0, run: tc qdisc show dev eth0 and tc class show dev eth0 to get the exact applied rules.\n- If the netem/tbf rules are unintended, remove them with: tc qdisc del dev eth0 root (or adjust/delete the specific qdiscs/classes).\n- Inspect how the rules were applied (cron, init scripts, automation/orchestration tool, or admin actions): check system logs, /etc/rc.local, systemd units, and any configuration management tool runs.\n\nIf you want, I can fetch the exact tc outputs and suggest the precise tc delete/replace commands and checks to prevent recurrence.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1977, "output_tokens": 181, "total_tokens": 2158, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
